6 An Act relating to solid waste management; exempting
combustor entities subject to certain oversight from
7 subsequent regulation; providing for codification;
and declaring an emergency.
8
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
11 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-10-206 of Title 27A, unless
13 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 Any municipal waste combustor subject to oversight under 40
15 C.F.R., Part 60, Subpart Eb, and regulation by the Department of
16 Environmental Quality shall be exempt from any subsequent regulation
17 by the Department of Environmental Quality relating to general-
18 purpose waste incineration or incineration of specified waste
19 sources, including, but not limited to: biomedical waste; hospital,
20 medical, and infectious waste; commercial solid waste; and
21 industrial solid waste.
22 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
